            "answer_text": "You had to get approval from the warden or deputy warden, have a model inmate status or so many days misconduct free, and any other hoop they wanted you to jump through cleared and then you could have an instrument approved. Only a few inmates I saw had this privilege and guitars were held at a specific location and could only be used in the yard or outside in the \u201cplay area\u201d. Due to the strings and metal you were not allowed to have it in your living space be it a cell or open or dorm like housing unit. ",
